.TH A2-SHORTCUTS 1 "October 2025" "a2 Manual"

.SH NAME
a2-shortcuts \- Keyboard shortcuts for the a2 editor

.SH DESCRIPTION
This page provides a comprehensive list of keyboard shortcuts for use in `a2`.

.SH GLOBAL SHORTCUTS
These shortcuts work in most modes.
.TP
.B Ctrl+] / Ctrl+[
Navigate to the next/previous window (split).
.TP
.B Alt+n / Alt+m
Navigate to the next/previous workspace.
.TP
.B Alt+x
Close the active window.
.TP
.B Ctrl+w
Create a new empty workspace.
.TP
.B Alt+Enter
Create a new vertical split window.
.TP
.B Alt+.
Cycle through available window layouts (e.g., vertical, horizontal, grid).
.TP
.B Alt+r
Rotate windows within the current layout.
.TP
.B Alt+[1-9]
Move the active window to the specified workspace.
.TP
.B Alt+[!,@,#,$,%,^,&,*,(]
Swap the active window with the window at the specified position (1-9).

.SH PALETTES & FINDERS
.TP
.B Alt+t
Open the unified Command Palette. By default, it fuzzy-finds files. Use `>` to search for commands, and `@` to search for symbols in the current file.
.TP
.B Alt+f
Open the Fuzzy Finder to specifically search for and open any file in the project.
.TP
.B Alt+b
Show a list of recently opened files.
.TP
.B Alt+s
Start a project-wide content search (grep) that runs in the background.
.TP
.B Alt+g, g
Open the directory navigator to quickly change the current working directory.

.SH NORMAL MODE
The default mode for navigation and commands.
.TP
.B i
Enter .B Insert Mode.
.TP
.B v
Enter .B Visual Mode.
.TP
.B :
Enter .B Command Mode.
.TP
.B o / l / k / รง / Arrow Keys
Navigate character by character.
.TP
.B G / g
Jump to the end / start of the file.
.TP
.B K / ร / Home / End
Jump to the start / end of the current line.
.TP
.B O / L / Page Up / Page Down
Navigate up / down by a page.
.TP
.B Alt+w / Alt+b
Move to the next / previous word.
.TP
.B u / U
Create a new line above/below the current line and enter Insert Mode.
.TP
.B yy
Yank (copy) the current line to the local register.
.TP
.B p / P
Paste from the local / global register after the cursor.
.TP
.B m
If text has been cut with 'm' in Visual Mode, pastes it at the cursor location.
.TP
.B Ctrl+f
Find text (supports regular expressions).
.TP
.B Ctrl+d / Ctrl+a
Find the next / previous occurrence of the last search term.
.TP
.B Ctrl+Del / Ctrl+k
Delete the current line.
.TP
.B q[a-z]
Start or stop recording a macro into the specified register.
.TP
.B @[a-z]
Playback a macro from the specified register.
.TP
.B @@
Repeat the last played macro.
.TP
.B Alt+c
Toggle comment on the current line.

.SH INSERT MODE
For typing text.
.TP
.B Esc
Return to .B Normal Mode.
.TP
.B Ctrl+o
Enter Normal Mode for a single command, then return to Insert Mode.
.TP
.B Tab
Context-aware: Indents if at start of a line, otherwise triggers code completion.
.TP
.B Ctrl+p / Ctrl+l
Create a new line above / below the current line.
.TP
.B ( [ { " '
Auto-closes the pair and places the cursor inside.

.SH VISUAL MODE
For selecting text.
.TP
.B s
Start or end a character-wise selection.
.TP
.B y
Yank (copy) the selection to the window's local register.
.TP
.B Ctrl+y
Yank the selection to the global register.
.TP
.B Alt+y
Copy the selection to the system clipboard.
.TP
.B m
Cut the selection to the special "move" register. Press 'm' in Normal Mode to paste.
.TP
.B Alt+Tab / Shift+Tab
Indent / un-indent the selected block of text.
.TP
.B Alt+c
Toggle comment on the selected lines.

.SH EXPLORER MODE
Active in the file explorer window.
.TP
.B j,k / Arrow Keys
Navigate up and down the file list.
.TP
.B Enter
Open a file or enter a directory.
.TP
.B q
Close the explorer window.
.TP
.B r
Rename the selected file or directory.
.TP
.B n
Create a new file in the current directory.
.TP
.B N
Create a new directory in the current directory.
.TP
.B c / x
Copy / Cut the selected file or directory.
.TP
.B v
Paste the copied/cut file or directory.
.TP
.B d
Delete the selected file or directory (with confirmation).

.SH MULTI-KEY SEQUENCES (ALT)
Press the first key, release, then press the second.
.TP
.B Alt+d, d
Open a new workspace and start a GDB session.
.TP
.B Alt+d, e
Open the Fuzzy Finder (same as Alt+f).
.TP
.B Alt+g, a
Run `git add -u` in a new terminal window.
.TP
.B Alt+g, s
Run `git status` in a new terminal window.
.TP
.B Alt+p, c
Paste from the system clipboard.
.TP
.B Alt+p, a / Alt+p, u
Paste the editor's local buffer above/below the current line.
.TP
.B Alt+p, P / Alt+p, U
Paste the editor's global buffer above/below the current line.

